<cite id="CITEREFLebow2003" class="citation book cs1">Lebow, Richard Ned (2003). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=SMoGlv7UrBkC"><i>The Tragic Vision of Politics: Ethics, Interests and Orders</i></a>. Cambridge University Press. pp. xi. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-521-53485-7" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-521-53485-7"><bdi>978-0-521-53485-7</bdi></a>. <q>I too am a realist</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Tragic+Vision+of+Politics%3A+Ethics%2C+Interests+and+Orders&amp;rft.pages=xi&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2003&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-521-53485-7&amp;rft.aulast=Lebow&amp;rft.aufirst=Richard+Ned&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DSMoGlv7UrBkC&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARichard+Ned+Lebow" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-:Ma&amp;Kang-9">
<span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-:Ma&amp;Kang_9-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1238218222">
